				<div class="comment-body"><p>Any two members (supporting or attending) of the current Worldcon can submit proposals to change the Hugo Awards rules by amending the World Science Fiction Society Constitution. Only attending members may be at the Business Meeting at Worldcon where the proposals are debated and discussed. Anything that passes two consecutive Worldcons&#8217; Business Meetings becomes part of the WSFS Constitution. Contact the <a href="http://sasquan.org/business-meeting/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">2015 Worldcon Business Meeting</a> for more information and for help drafting proposals.</p>
</div>

