				<div class="comment-body"><p>Incidentally, I have seen no realistic proposal to take away any individual&#8217;s nominating privileges other than some that propose removing the extension of such rights to the members of the previous and following Worldcons. Remember that inasmuch as WSFS membership is defined as the members of the <em>current</em> Worldcon, allowing members from other years to make nominations is a relaxation of the principle of allowing only members to participate in the process. Even if that happens, no individual would be prohibited from nominated based on that member&#8217;s ideology; everyone would still be allowed to join the current Worldcon.</p>
</div>

