				<div class="comment-body"><p>The problem you face, Steve, is that any such wording will be seized upon and the practice of authors listing what they published last year and of groups like NESFA and BASFA creating their own rather chaotic recommendation lists is the same thing as a curated slate. You and I know the difference, and I suspect most of the people behind this year&#8217;s efforts do as well, but there may well be people who really can&#8217;t see any distinction between them.</p>
